              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 my-4">
                Gone through the documentation, yet Confused?
                Check out the tutorials to get a better understanding of Confuscript.
                Friendly warning: Even I don't understand Confuscript.
              </p>
              <a href="/docs/tutorials/factorials" class="inline-block bg-red-700 hover:bg-red-800 text-white text-lg font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">
                TUTORIALS
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto dark:text-white md:py-32 md:flex md:flex-wrap">
      <div class="p-8 md:w-1/2">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Why Did I Do This?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg my-8">
          Nowadays, every Programming Language follows the same syntax and structure. I wanted to change that! Challenge the very fundamentals of programming.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-8 md:w-1/2">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Make it more confusing</h2>
        <p class="text-lg my-8">
          I'm just one single person, and I can't make Confuscript as confusing as I want it to be. So, I need your help!
